1. Gstreamer is a multimedia engine.
  2. For example, we might have an element that likes to create flowers !
    Its job is to let elements communicate in a standard way
    Creating flowers is all well and good, but someday you have to send them !
    This is what PADS are for.
    Pads are the ports through which data is sent.
    An element can have a source pad only, when it is a producer
    And it can have a sink pad only, when it is a consumer
    Or it can have both, when it is a filter
    Let's link these elements
    So that data can flow between them
    This new element is a sink, in our case it is a screen which will display whatever we send in its general direction
  3. This design has obvious advantages
    It makes it very easy to add and remove elements on the fly.
    Here is another example.
  4. Gnonlin is the plugin that makes pipelines dynamic
    Let's say we want to play two clips one after another
    Gnonlin will let the first clip play for a certain duration
    Then it will discard the first clip and connect the second one
    This design allows us to create complex timelines, while still leveraging the full power of gstreamer !
